    <p style="margin-left: 8; margin-right: 8"><font size="2"><font face="Microsoft Sans Serif" size="2">

<font size=2><table width="100%" bgcolor="#004b97"><font color=#d2d200><b>Griohin the Wise</b></font>&nbsp;&nbsp;<font size=1><a style="color: #ffffff" href="mailto:jcsmith@amazinghideaways.com?subject=Regarding: Griohin the Wise">Submit Info</a></font></table>
<font color=white>
<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Level:</font></b> 68-68<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Sociality:</b></font> Social<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Classification:</b></font> Rare_Monster<br>
<b><font color=#d2d200>Known Habitats:</b></font> Reef of Coirnav<br>

<br><b>Special Attacks:</b><br>
<a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=spellsbrdcomplete&eqspells.spell_name=%22Tidal%20Freeze%22">Tidal Freeze</a>
<br>







<br><b><font color=#d2d200>Description:</b></font><br>- Cold based (-350) PBAE does up to 2000 points of damage and stuns the taret for 5 seconds. It has a radius of 250 but a recast of 60.<BR>- Rampages<BR>- Magic Slowable(Mitigated)<BR><BR><b>Spawn and Scouting</b><BR><BR>Griohin the Wise can be tracked from the zone in. You can <a href="http://www.eqspoilers.com/cgi-bin/eqs/webdata_pro.pl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=eqmap1&eqzones.zone_name=%22Reef%20of%20Coirnav%22">this map</a> for a visual representation of where he spawns. You can invis right to his room to search for him if you can not track.<BR> <BR>He is a three day spawn.<BR><BR><b>What You Need</b><BR><BR>Griohin the Wise is a tricky fight. You will need at least three solid tanks, a six cleric complete healing chain and lots of patch healing. MGB Spirit of the Wood and EE are a major plus for this encounter.<BR><BR>You will need 40 or more players to have a good shot at killing him.<BR><BR><b>Preparation</b><BR><BR>Clerics and Druids with MGB and Spirit of the Wood or EE should save their MGBs for the fight.<BR><BR>Be sure that all of your tanks have some form of levitation. This will prevent them from dropping down as they are idle in the water. Everyone should also be wearing a water breathing item, or have the spell cast on them. <BR><BR>Everyone should have their cold resistance buffed as high as possible. Circle of Seasons and Summer stack. By stacking these two you will put most players are close to maximum cold resistance. Although his AE is seldomly resisted completely, you can resist it partially.<BR><BR><b>Getting There</b><BR><BR>From the entrance you should head in to the first large pool and clear the mobs in the pool. Once the pool is clear move the raid in to the left through the tunnel on the left hand side. Take a right when the tunnel forks and then take another right. The room you will now be facing is where Griohin the Wise spawns. I recommend pulling all of the trash mobs in to this hallway until he is there alone. <BR><BR><b>The Fight</b><BR><BR>I recommend clearing the entire room until Groihin is solo. After that you can either move inside of the room and kill him there, or if you are low on DPS you can pull him to the hallway. <BR><BR>Griohin hits for about 2100 per attack and rampages. He can be slowed with magic, but mitigates it. A six cleric healing chain should be enough on the main tank. You are going want to have at least two more healers dedicated to the rampage tank.<BR><BR>The key to this victory over Griohin is not in dealing with his melee, it is in dealing with his AE. Griohin has a cold based (-350) PBAE which does up to 2000 points of damage and stuns the target for 5 seconds. It has a radius of 250, but a recast of 60. The dangerous part of this fight is in the few seconds after his AE lands. The cleric chain will be stunned at this point, everyone else needs to patch. The stun can last for up to five seconds, which means your main tank needs to survive during this time period without heals. As a result it is very important to keep him near full health at all times. Patches are dire in this encounter.<BR><BR>Those with MGB Spirit of the Wood and EE should save them for the encounter. Use an MGB healing chain during the fight. This will heal players of the damage that they take in between AEs, and will help keep the main tank up after the stun.<BR><BR>I recommend weaponshield tanking him to start and using that time to eat the first AE. You then have a minute before the next. Maximize your DPS and drop him as quickly as possible. It is important to have your second and third tanks ready to step in immediately if the main tank dies. There is a good possibility that your main tank will fall after the AE, be ready for it.<BR><BR><b>Loot</b><BR><BR>Griohin the Wise can drop one or two loots. He does not drop elemental molds, but his drops are decent. They include a bard only Lute, a Flowing Thought 3 ring and leather leggings with Aura of Daring.<BR><BR>In addition to these loots he can also drop runes and spectral parchments.<br>

<br><b>Known Drops</b>:<br>

<A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Lute of Flowing Waters%22">Lute of Flowing Waters</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Seaweed Woven Leggings%22">Seaweed Woven Leggings</A><br> <A HREF="webdata_pro%2epl?_cgifunction=Search&_layout=equipmentfull&eqequipment%2eitem_name=%22Ring of Algae%22">Ring of Algae</A><br>

